Document Title: Regulatory Directive â€“ Fire Safety Compliance 2025
Issued By: Commissioner of Metro Rail Safety (CMRS)
Date: 02 September 2025

As per directive CMRS/2025/FS-12, all metro operators are instructed to comply with the updated National Fire Safety Code by 01 October 2025.

Mandatory Requirements:

1. Detection Systems: Smoke detectors to be installed at 9-meter intervals in underground concourses and tunnels.

2. Fire Drills: Conduct quarterly evacuation drills; reports to be submitted to CMRS within 15 days.

3. Cabling Standards: Upgrade to fire-resistant cabling conforming to BIS IS-7098.

4. Passenger Communication: Emergency instructions to be broadcast in English and Malayalam, supported by visual aids.

5. Signage: Evacuation maps displayed every 50 meters in stations and depot corridors.

Compliance Timeline:

- Initial gap analysis to be completed by 15 September 2025.

- Implementation plan to be submitted to CMRS by 20 September 2025.

- Full compliance mandatory by 01 October 2025.

Audit & Enforcement:

- CMRS inspectors will conduct random inspections beginning October 2025.

- Non-compliance will attract penalties under Metro Railways (Operations & Maintenance) Act, 2002, Section 22-B.

- Repeat violations may result in suspension of operating license until corrective measures are implemented.

Responsibility:
KMRL Safety Department shall oversee implementation in coordination with Operations, Engineering, and HR (for training). Monthly compliance report to be presented to KMRL Board and CMRS.

This directive cancels all previous fire safety circulars issued prior to January 2024 and remains valid until superseded by new legislation.